00:34:45.317 --> 00:34:48.153
wrote software that
automatically collected the

00:34:48.153 --> 00:34:53.491
entire inventory of what we
considered to be our main

00:34:53.491 --> 00:34:56.528
competitors. And this channel
actually made it really easy for

00:34:56.528 --> 00:35:00.598
us to do this because they
actually list the top resellers

00:35:00.598 --> 00:35:07.372
on the channel. So we would look
at all of their inventory. And

00:35:07.372 --> 00:35:10.442
we would do it again. And
basically the delta, the

00:35:10.442 --> 00:35:13.678
difference between these two
over maybe like a day or a

00:35:13.678 --> 00:35:17.515
week's time would give us
metadata to describe what they

00:35:17.515 --> 00:35:22.187
sold and for how much, and also
what didn't sell during that

00:35:22.187 --> 00:35:26.691
period. So this is how we
learned about our competition.

00:35:26.691 --> 00:35:30.762
And we did this a lot. So the
more of this we did, the more

00:35:30.762 --> 00:35:35.900
metadata we got that described
what sold, how much, how long

00:35:35.900 --> 00:35:40.338
their inventory stayed online
before it was sold, and again,

00:35:40.338 --> 00:35:44.676
what didn't sell. And we're able
to do this because if you look

00:35:44.676 --> 00:35:47.712
at the inventory one day, you
look at it another day, if

00:35:47.712 --> 00:35:51.883
something is missing here, you
assume that it sold for the last

00:35:51.883 --> 00:35:57.022
known price, right? And this is,
I mean, you can tell so much

00:35:57.022 --> 00:36:02.927
about businesses that sell
unique or probably or likely

00:36:02.927 --> 00:36:06.331
unique items. If you think of
all the businesses out there

00:36:06.331 --> 00:36:09.534
that put all of their inventory
out online, you can study this

00:36:09.534 --> 00:36:12.637
to the point where you can
almost do their books for them.

00:36:12.637 --> 00:36:17.308
You know what their money is
coming in. So, okay. One more.

00:36:17.308 --> 00:36:21.046
How do we protect our
investments? Well, we have

00:36:21.046 --> 00:36:24.215
software that looks for
situations like this. So if

00:36:24.215 --> 00:36:29.120
we're seller C and our price is
19.50 and we're competitors with

00:36:29.120 --> 00:36:34.893
D and E, we have software that
will go out and flag situations

00:36:34.893 --> 00:36:38.630
like this, where people, for
whatever reason, they're dumping

00:36:38.630 --> 00:36:42.967
stuff for below market value. So
we have software that goes off

00:36:42.967 --> 00:36:45.203
and we immediately buy these
things. This is how we kind of

00:36:45.203 --> 00:36:50.875
pseudo-manipulate our markets.
So if we find things that are

00:36:50.875 --> 00:36:53.411
underpriced like that, we buy
them and they become our

00:36:53.411 --> 00:36:57.415
inventory and we're protecting
our investment. But again, we

00:36:57.415 --> 00:37:00.885
